Primary Design Engineer - Alstom Indonesia
Primary Design Engineer  -
Primary Design Engineer
Responsibilities
Layout Engineering: Knowledge of all sizing criteria. Able to optimise a layout integrating all constraints linked to erection, maintenance and operation of a Substation.Primary Design Tool (CAD): Ensure daily suppport to CAD users, to organise training, to determine and then supervise the necessary development of the tool.HV Material: Good knowledge of most of HV material and hardware, mastery of the standards associated to.Structures Sizing: Ensure daily support on structures calculation, to organise training and to supervise a subcontractor.Earthing Grid: Ensure a daily support on earthing grid calculation, to organise training and to supervise a subcontractor & able to optimise the solutions.Tubular Busbar:  Ensure a daily support on tubular busbar calculation, to organise training and to supervise a subcontractorElectroMagnetic Compatibility for Primary: calculate electrical fields and magnetic fields for HV cables, HV coils, transformers, CTs, VTS…and to supervise subcontracting studies. Knows how to compute the corona ineption voltage on equipment design and is able to optimise a layout according to the EM constraints.Audible noise: Able to perform and supervise audible noise studies. Able to optimise a layout according to the results of the study and the customer requirements.   Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree, Master's Degree / Post Graduate Degree, majoring in Electrical or Civil EngineeringExperience working in similiar industries will be an advantageAt least 5 years of experience in related fieldFluent in English
Requirements
